 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugekkobear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gekkobear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 6:21:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  which pet</span><hr size=1> I used unfocused fire at lvl 29.  He did pretty good.  I tend to stick with fire, as I tire of recasting the DS myself... just lazy I guess.<br>
<br>
I led off the fights with ward summoned (yes, the weak one, my evo wasn't maxxed at the time) and just healed my pet.  The weaker heal (50 hps for 25 mana) is more efficients, but occasionaly I'd need to use the big one to keep up (100 mana, 150-160 hps?).  <br>
<br>
When you zone in there is a tower.  Pulling them most of the way up the hill seems to stop them from wandering back to get adds.<br>
<br>
The elementals will assist others of their kind, but not elementals of other kinds (i.e. if 2 earth and a water are standing together, you can single pull the water).  Be sure to pull from max distance and run when pulling earth, as that root can make things difficult.<br>
<br>
I got quite a few lava rocks, essence of wind, swirling mist.  and a couple windstones.  Also I saw 3 of the forst type of &quot;special&quot; elementals (hulking?), which all dropped the lore 10AC 5 str gauntlets (sell for 25-50 plat easy, maybe more if you want to stop killing to look for a buyer).  I didn't see any iron oxide, but that was likely just my bad luck.<br>
<br>
Not bad exp at 29. steady pulls. At 30 about 10% went light blue, and at 31 about 25-30% were light blue (so I left).<br>
<br>
Oh, and for teamnoir, its easy to miss the weapons proccing, you have to watch carefully to see the target &quot;stagger&quot;.  I didn't really keep track of proc's per fight, just knew they happened.<br>
<br>
Gekkobear (now Mandelbrot and Riemann on Rathe).<br>
<br>
